{{ill|Taikodani Inari Shrine|ja|太皷谷稲成神社}} is a [[Shinto shrine]] located in [[Japan]]. It is a [[Beppyo shrine]], or a shrine that is particularly notable in a certain way with a significant history to it.<ref>{{Cite web |title=別表神社とは？御朱印めぐりに参考になる「別表神社一覧」とマップ {{!}} 開運戦隊ゴシュインジャー |url=https://jinja-gosyuin.com/beppyou/ |access-date=2023-04-02 |website=jinja-gosyuin.com}}</ref> It is an [[Inari shrine]] dedicated to [[Inari Ōkami]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |last=TOKYO |first=COPYRIGHT © CHUGOKU ＋ SHIKOKU × |title=Taikodani Inari Shrine {{!}} CHUGOKU＋SHIKOKU×TOKYO (JAPAN) |url=https://www.chushikokuandtokyo.org/spot_236/ |access-date=2023-10-19 |website=www.chushikokuandtokyo.org |language=en}}</ref>

It is one of the five great Inari shrines of Japan.<ref name=":0" /><ref>https://zekkeijapan.com/spot/index/1771/</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web |title=日本吉 - NIPPON-KICHI |url=https://nippon-kichi.jp/article_list.do?kwd=3013&ml_lang=en |access-date=2023-10-19 |website=nippon-kichi.jp}}</ref><ref>https://japantravel.navitime.com/en/area/jp/guide/NTJnews0321-en/</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=If you are looking for a sightseeing taxi in Karuizawa, come to “Matsuba Taxi” |url=https://www.matsuba-taxi.com/eng/smart/detail.php?pg=tourism_saku |access-date=2023-10-19 |website=www.matsuba-taxi.com}}</ref>

Kamei Norisada founded it in 1744<ref name=":1" />
[[ja:太皷谷稲成神社]]

